      <hedline>
        <hl1>Hong Kong Shop</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Phyllis H Wollman letter on Mark Landler's April 16 travel article describes stores at Star Ferry Terminal in Hong Kongr</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Speaking of ''Hong Kong Is Humming Again'' (April 16) by Mark Landler, one of the city's biggest attractions for me has always been the pharmacy on the second floor of the Star Ferry Terminal. In this exotic-smelling shop one can purchase the finest French perfumes at low prices.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Speaking of ''Hong Kong Is Humming Again'' (April 16) by Mark Landler, one of the city's biggest attractions for me has always been the pharmacy on the second floor of the Star Ferry Terminal. In this exotic-smelling shop one can purchase the finest French perfumes at low prices.</p>
        <p>In other shops in the terminal, I found antique jewelry and fabrics, beautiful enough to be framed as works of art, at attractive prices.</p>
        <p>PHYLLIS H. WOLLMAN  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
